SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 439
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to recognize Joseph Galbato III on the occasion
of his retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we should honor those citizens who have performed
with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their years of public service; and
WHEREAS, Joseph Galbato III of Franklin is one such estimable person, who has
served with distinction since October 2011 as the Tennessee Department of Transportation's
(TDOT) Chief of Administration, Deputy Commissioner, and Chief Financial Officer (CFO); and
WHEREAS, Mr. Galbato will be taking his much-deserved retirement this year, bringing
to a close fourteen years of steady, devoted leadership at TDOT; and
WHEREAS, as TDOT's Chief of Administration, Deputy Commissioner, and CFO, Joe
Galbato is responsible for financial oversight of the department, including budget preparation,
budget management, and federal highway reimbursement; and
WHEREAS, he also oversees several divisions of TDOT, including Human Resources,
Finance, Information Technology, Procurement, Civil Rights, and Internal Audit and was integral
in the development and implementation of several key initiatives to modernize the department,
including Empowering People, Influencing Culture (EPIC) and Integrated Program Delivery
(IPD); and
WHEREAS, Joe Galbato has worked to ensure the financial integrity of the department
by instituting several financial controls regarding TDOT spending, initiating cash principles, and
modernizing forecast methods; he has been a trusted resource for the General Assembly and
the executive branch; and
