WHEREAS, highly regarded by his colleagues and those he serves, Mr. Galbato is an
active member of the American Association of State Highway and Transportation Officials and
served as TDOT's interim commissioner from October 2021 to May 2022; and
WHEREAS, Joe Galbato was born in Jamestown, New York, to Dr. Joseph Galbato, Jr.,
and Alyce Wolfe Galbato; he graduated magna cum laude from the State University of New
York, where he earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration with a
concentration in Finance; and
WHEREAS, he was a four-year member of the State University of New York's varsity
baseball team and joined the Philadelphia Phillies as a free agent for spring training in 1987;
and
WHEREAS, prior to joining TDOT, Mr. Galbato served as CFO for multiple healthcare
companies in Nashville, including Alive Hospice, HCCA International, and Envoy/WebMD; and
WHEREAS, a talented singer-songwriter, Mr. Galbato has released multiple records of
original music, a passion that he intends to pursue further in retirement; and
WHEREAS, he will also spend more time with his wife, Linda, and their three children,
Joseph IV, Katelyn, and Thomas; and
WHEREAS, throughout his estimable career, Joe Galbato has demonstrated the utmost
professionalism, ability, and integrity; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we extend to Joseph Galbato III our heartfelt wishes
for a happy and fulfilling retirement and every continued success in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
